results.name: Permutation of natural numbers induced by Catalan Automorphism *A089859 acting on the binary trees/parenthesizations encoded by A014486/A063171.
comment: This automorphism effects the following transformation on the unlabeled rooted plane binary trees (letters A, B, C refer to arbitrary subtrees located on those nodes and () stands for an implied terminal node).
See the Karttunen OEIS-Wiki link for a detailed explanation of how to obtain a given integer sequence from this definition.
link: A. Karttunen, C-program for computing this sequence
Index entries for signature-permutations induced by Catalan automorphisms
program: (Scheme functions implementing this automorphism on list-structures/S-expressions, both constructive (*A089859) and destructive (*A089859!) versions:)
(define (*A089859 s) (cond ((not (pair? s)) s) ((not (pair? (cdr s))) (cons (cdr s) (car s))) (else (cons (cons (cddr s) (cadr s)) (car s)))))
(define (*A089859! s) (cond ((pair? s) (cond ((pair? (cdr s)) (*A069770! (cdr s)) (*A069770! s)) (else (*A069770! s))))) s)
xref: Row 15 of A089840. Inverse of A089863. a(n) = A089854(A069770(n)) = A069770(A089850(n)). A089864 is the "square" of this permutation.
Number of cycles: A089407. Max. cycle size & LCM of all cycle sizes: A040002 (in each range limited by A014137 and A014138).
